5:
Does anyone know what happened
to the pudding that was in the fridge?
9:
Was it labeled or something?
Somebody probably just ate it.
13: I mean... That would be fine, I guess...
15:
But recently, a lot of snacks have
been disappearing from the fridge.
20:
Is that so? I doubt Starview Village is
home to thieves, but perhaps we
should stake things out tonight and
see.
24:
Honestly, I don't mind if somebody's
just having a late night snack...
33:
Ohhh boy! There's so much here
today.
37: A... child? What is she doing here?
57:
No, I think she's just using some sort
of magic to conceal herself!
64:
No doubt about it, I definitely sense
someone else in this room.
68:
Hey, you can come out. We're not
gonna eat you.
79:
Whoa, why are you crying?! D-don't
worry, we're not mad or anything!
88:
You said your name was Fuku,
correct?
90:
Judging from your attire, I would
guess that you're from Yamato. How
did you get here?
95:
...Dunno. I just appeared here
suddenly one day.
98:
And you arrived alone? What of your
parents? Did any adults come with
you?
102: No? It's just been me the whole time.
104:
So I've been sneaking into and
sleeping in a lot of people's houses.
112:
I guess you've done all right for
yourself so far. Nobody's noticed you?
117:
Oh! Uh... Only a few, but I just
disappeared right away!
121:
Just like you did earlier. Who taught
you how to do that?
126:
Um... Nobody? I was just born like
this.
135:
Urk! Uh... Don't be silly, th-those
aren't even real! I'm a totally normal
human!
143:
You don't believe me?! I'm definitely
not a fortune-granting zashiki
warashi, or anything!
148:
Take it easy, kid. We're not yokai
hunters.
153:
We've got plenty of yokai friends,
after all.
158:
All the same, perhaps we should
inform Suizen of this situation.
163:
Oh, right! Suizen! He's the Chair of
the Diviners' Commission, and...
171:
I don't... I don't like those people! I
don't want to be sealed away
again...
176: ...Got it. We'll keep you a secret, okay?
184:
Why not? If you were some scary
giant we might have hesitated, but...
187:
It doesn't look like you're too
dangerous.
192:
H-hey! I'm tougher than I look, you
know!
197:
In any case, you can take it easy
here.
199:
You're welcome to stay in Starview
Village, and we'll help you if you've
got somewhere you need to go.
202:
R-really? You're not going to shut
me away?
204: I can just come and go as I please?
218: We're happy to have you with us.
